summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 23902, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of Garfield Street from Queen Anne Avenue to Fourth Avenue North, et al. in the City of Seattle, by paving with asphalt, etc. under Ordinance No. 20385, creating Local Improvement District No. 1980, prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement," approved April 19, 1910.
